headline: Home Depot (HD): Buy, Sell, or Hold Post Q1 Earnings?
summary: Over the last six months, Home Depot’s shares have sunk to $385.41, producing a disappointing 6.9% loss - a stark contrast to the S&P 500’s 3.6% gain. This was partly due to its softer quarterly results and might have investors contemplating their next move.
